cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.LG

This paper deals with the analysis of vulnerabilities in smart contracts, which are executable objects hosted on blockchains. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as software engineering (cs.SE) since it involves analyzing and reasoning about software behavior. The paper also employs symbolic analysis and concrete validation techniques, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the use of machine learning techniques for identifying vulnerabilities could also be considered as falling under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
